In another embodiment, the invention relates to a method of ameliorating the adverse affects of photodynamic therapy ("PDT"), or enhancing the selectivity of PDT, in a subject in need of PDT treatment, comprising the steps of:


a. administering to the subject an amount of photosensitive agent effective to selectively accumulate in target cells;


b. administering to the subject an apoptosis-regulating amount of at least one cysteine or serine protease inhibitor that:

a. inhibits the conversion of the pro-enzyme form of CPP32 to its enzymatically-active form;


b. blocks the proteolytic action of activated CPP32 against its cellular substrates; or


c. both.
